{
  "texts": [
    "The second part of the common architecture transforms the extracted features by applying a sequence of 4 attention layers on the extracted patches, which maintain the dimension of the layer.",
    "Moreover, the same gate layout, i.e.",
    "the butterfly circuit, is used for all circuits that compose the quantum layers.",
    "Finally, the last part of the neural network is classical, which linearly projects the extracted features and outputs the predicted label.",
    "Simulation ResultsA summary of the simulation results is shown in Table 3 where the area under receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve (AUC) and the accuracy (ACC) are reported as evaluation metrics."
  ]
}